text.text:
March 12, 2024 (Tuesday evening) -- My friend took me here, the place is richly decorated with traditional South Indian statues and artifacts, with well spaced table placements. The menu was broad and covered a lot of South Indian delicacies that one won't see in a typical Indian restaurant outside India, which are dominated by North Indian rotis/naans and gravies. So, this is the kind of restaurant you take your foreign friend/client to -- exotic, authentic, and pleasant.

We had the following.
1. Navaratna dosai -- A normal ghee (clarified butter) dosai with dry fruits -- such as almond (badam), tooty-frooty, apple, pineapple, cashew, cherry -- inside the fold of the dosai.
This was sweet and the `ghee'ness was super!
The accompanying sambar and onion chutney were spicy to the right levels, the coconut-bengal gram chutney was very soft.
I ate two cups of each of the three.

2. Roti and pudhina paratha -- were normal.
3. Methi Malai mutter and Paneer pasanda -- the gravies were soft (less spicy) and flavourful.
We actually ordered the 'Methi makkai palak', but we were served (and billed) Methi malai mutter.

4. On the house vadaam (sort of a rice flour dough deep fry) at the beginning and sweet beeda (beetel leaf folded with sweet stuffing inside) were given.
I was never a fan or regular eater of beeda, but I tried it that day. It was nice and juicy, the sweetness and leafness were well balanced.

5. The servers bring around 4 pickles now and then. I tried the puli inji (tamarind and ginger), and mango ginger.  Both were very good.

The prices are very high ~Rs. 1600 for two, but the quality of food , ambience, and service were very good.

text.text:
Our first writers Cafe experience, this establishment managed to elevate my day, offering a delightful blend of ambiance, an extensive menu, impeccable services, delectable flavors, and affordability. It stands out as an irresistible haven for students and individuals seeking a serene environment to delve into their work while savoring a steaming cup of mocha.

Our time there was nothing short of exceptional, as we explored an array of mouthwatering dishes that left an indelible mark on our taste buds. From the standard chicken pizza to the succulent chicken skewers, the flavorful mushroom white sauce pasta, and the enticing veg cheese balls, each dish surpassed expectations in terms of quality and taste. The cafe mocha and hot chocolate further added to the overall delightful experience.

The allure extended to the frozen delights, featuring the irresistible salted caramel, the luscious red velvet cheesecake, and the rich Vanilla Madagascar ice creams. Each frozen treat provided a refreshing and indulgent conclusion to our culinary journey.

Remarkably, the total bill amounted to a mere 2500, a testament to the establishment's commitment to providing not just a gastronomic feast but also an affordable dining experience. This affordability factor becomes even more apparent when compared to other cafes, making it a standout choice for those conscious of their budget.

In essence, this place has mastered the art of creating a harmonious fusion of delectable cuisine, inviting atmosphere, attentive service, and reasonable pricing. It has become a go-to spot for those seeking a perfect blend of productivity and relaxation, encapsulated in the enjoyment of flavorful dishes and delightful beverages. Without a doubt, this establishment has secured its place as a memorable and cherished dining destination for us, leaving us eager for the next opportunity to indulge in its culinary offerings.

text.text:
Unfortunately, the Accord is one of the worst 5-star hotels we have stayed at in terms of rooms and service. The experience from using their website to leaving is at most a 3-star experience. The location is the best thing about this hotel.

We booked a room for 2 nights and the booking stated that check in was at 12pm. However, once we arrived there we were informed that check in was not till 2pm. Nothing was done to help the situation despite it being their mistake.

A few points:
- They are renovating rooms so make sure they do not give you a room next to one they are renovating because it will be extremely noisy.
- They charge for lost key cards which I have never experienced in a 5-star hotel.
- They only have a single driver for airport pickups and drop offs which is shocking for a hotel of this size.
- When trying to book a 24-hour check in, they complicated the process and tried to charge us more than the cost of just booking a stay for the previous night.
- Some of the staff can be very rude and would not honour late check out requests.
- Their website is incredibly difficult to use and breaks often. When you call the team, they simply deny it and state it is working.
- Some of the refurbished rooms have bathrooms where the water stagnates.

I'd recommend staying at the Hyatt Regency which is 10 minutes down the road. The location is not as good as the Accord but it is an actual 5-star experience.
